    "body": "This is a little harder than it seems. For example, what happens if there are incompatible licenses in the flattened contract?\r\n\r\nIf you are just using it for debugging in remix, I think the easiest solution is to just run a regex and remove all spdx comments. If you are on a UNIX system, this can be done with a one liner:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhh flatten | grep -v '// SPDX' > Flattened.sol\r\n```",
